SIMPLE: bet
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bet
<hw>Bet</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. from OE.
<ets>abet</ets> abetting, OF. <ets>abet</ets>, fr. <ets>abeter</ets> to
excite, incite. See <er>Abet</er>.]</ety> <def>That which is laid,
staked, or pledged, as between two parties, upon the event of a contest
or any contingent issue; the act of giving such a pledge; a wager.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Having made his <xex>bets</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Goldsmith.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bet</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Bet
<hw>Bet</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Bet</conjf>, <conjf>Betted</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Betting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To stake or pledge
upon the event of a contingent issue; to wager.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>John a Gaunt loved him well, and <qex>betted</qex> much money on
his head.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I'll <qex>bet</qex> you two to one I'll make him do it.</q>
<rj><qau>O. W. Holmes.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bet</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Bet
<hw>Bet</hw>, <def><pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> of <er>Beat</er>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bet</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Bet
<hw>Bet</hw>, <pos>a. & adv.</pos> <def>An early form of
<er>Better</er>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To go bet</b></col>, <cd>to go fast; to hurry.</cd>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

